               <p>I was in company with Mr. Redgrave. I met the prisoner in Turnmill-street, on the 12th of June, between the hours of eight and nine o'clock in the morning; I saw him come out of a house which lay under a suspicion of receiving stolen goods, with a bundle; I stopped him, and in the bundle I found this wearing apparel (producing the several articles mentioned in the indictment.)</p>
